                <head>411. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Dean Rusk</persName> left for
                    Geneva on July 20. The Secretary held a series of discussions, which were
                    essentially courtesy calls, with the other Foreign Ministers, Indian Defense
                    Minister Krishna Menon, and <persName corresp="#p_SPP1">Souvanna
                        Phouma</persName> and Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_QP1">Quinim
                        Pholsena</persName> on July 22. Memoranda of the discussions are in
                    Department of State, Central Files, 110.11–RU/7–2262; ibid., Secretary’s
                    Memoranda of Conversation: Lot 65 D 330; and ibid., Conference Files: Lot 65 D
                    533, CF 2134–2141.</p>
                <p>On July 23, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD1">Rusk</persName> signed for the
                    United States the Declaration on the Neutrality of Laos. Attached to the
                    Declaration was a 20-article Protocol. The texts of the Declaration and Protocol
                    are printed in <hi rend="italic">American Foreign Policy: Current Documents,
                        1962</hi>, pages 1075–1083.</p>
            </div>
